verbose_text: miR-133b regulates mammalian sterile 20 like kinase (MST2), cell division control protein 42 homolog (CDC42), and ras homolog gene family member A (RHOA) and consequently activates the mitogen activated protein kinase 1 (MAPK1) and v-akt murine thymoma viral oncogene homolog 1 (AKT1) signaling pathways and facilitates malignant transformation.
